---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="AudioSRT for CapCut — Free Subtitles for Shorts and Reels" description="Generate styled subtitles for CapCut, Reels, and TikTok content. Free 9:16 portrait support and burned-in subtitle video export." canonical="https://audiosrt.com/integrations/capcut">
  <Header />
  <main class="lp-main">

    <section class="lp-hero">
      <span class="lp-badge">9:16 Portrait · Burned-In MP4</span>
      <h1 class="lp-h1">AudioSRT for CapCut<br><span class="lp-accent">Subtitles for Shorts and Reels</span></h1>
      <p class="lp-intro">
        Short-form vertical video lives and dies by on-screen text. Most viewers watch TikTok, Reels, and Shorts with their phone on silent — if your captions aren't visible from the first frame, you've lost them. AudioSRT's 9:16 portrait canvas is built specifically for this format, letting you transcribe a clip, style the captions, and export a finished MP4 without touching CapCut's built-in caption tools.
      </p>
      <p class="lp-intro">
        The styling controls matter as much as the transcript quality. Font choice, color, stroke weight, and vertical position all affect how your captions read at mobile size and how consistent they look across your content. Set your style once, transcribe your clip, and export a finished video ready to upload directly to TikTok, Instagram Reels, or YouTube Shorts — no re-import into CapCut needed.
      </p>
      <a href="/#tool" class="lp-cta">Create styled subtitles →</a>
    </section>

    <section class="lp-steps-section" style="margin: 0 auto 48px;">
      <h2>The short-form subtitle workflow</h2>
      <div class="lp-steps">
        <div class="lp-step">
          <div class="lp-step-num">01</div>
          <h3>Upload your clip</h3>
          <p>Load an MP4, MOV, or WebM file — your edited vertical clip from CapCut, a screen recording, or a clip shot directly on your phone. Everything stays on your device.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="lp-step">
          <div class="lp-step-num">02</div>
          <h3>Style your captions</h3>
          <p>Switch to 9:16 portrait canvas and dial in your caption style — font, size, color, stroke, shadow, and vertical position. Preview how captions will look at mobile size before you commit to the export.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="lp-step">
          <div class="lp-step-num">03</div>
          <h3>Export finished MP4</h3>
          <p>Export the video with captions burned directly into the frame. The output is a single MP4 file — upload it to TikTok, Instagram Reels, or YouTube Shorts without any additional editing step.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="lp-features">
      <h2>Built for short-form creators</h2>
      <div class="lp-feature-grid">
        <div class="lp-feature-card">
          <div class="lp-feature-icon">📱</div>
          <h3>9:16 portrait canvas</h3>
          <p>The preview and export canvas is sized for vertical video from the start — not a landscape tool with a portrait mode bolted on. Captions render at the right size and position for mobile screens.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="lp-feature-card">
          <div class="lp-feature-icon">🎨</div>
          <h3>Full caption styling</h3>
          <p>Control font family, size, weight, color, stroke, drop shadow, and vertical placement. Build a style that matches your brand and use it consistently across all your clips.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="lp-feature-card">
          <div class="lp-feature-icon">🎬</div>
          <h3>Burned-in MP4 export</h3>
          <p>Captions are rendered directly into the video frame on export. The finished file works on every platform regardless of caption track support — no SRT file to manage separately.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="lp-feature-card">
          <div class="lp-feature-icon">🆓</div>
          <h3>Free 14-day trial</h3>
          <p>Video captioning features are available on the Starter plan. Start with a 14-day free trial — no credit card required to test the full workflow on your clips.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="lp-detail">
      <p class="lp-body">
        <strong>Also making long-form YouTube content?</strong> If you publish both Shorts and full-length videos, the <a href="/tools/youtube-captions" class="lp-inline-link">YouTube caption generator</a> covers the SRT/VTT upload workflow for long-form content alongside the burned-in export for Shorts.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="lp-cta-section">
      <h2>Create styled subtitles for your Shorts</h2>
      <p>Video features on the Starter plan — 14-day free trial, no credit card required.</p>
      <a href="/#tool" class="lp-cta">Start free trial →</a>
    </section>

  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
.lp-main { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: #1D1D1F; }
.lp-hero { text-align: center; padding: 80px 20px 60px; max-width: 760px; margin: 0 auto; }
.lp-badge { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; background: #EEEFFD; color: #6366F1; font-size: 12px; font-weight: 500; padding: 5px 14px; border-radius: 20px; border: 0.5px solid #C7C8F9; margin-bottom: 24px; }
.lp-h1 { font-size: clamp(28px, 4.5vw, 46px); font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.15; letter-spacing: -0.8px; margin-bottom: 16px; }
.lp-accent { color: #6366F1; }
.lp-intro { font-size: 15px; color: #6E6E73; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 32px; max-width: 560px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; }
.lp-cta { display: inline-block; background: #6366F1; color: #fff; padding: 13px 28px; border-radius: 10px; font-size: 15px; font-weight: 500; text-decoration: none; transition: background 0.15s; }
.lp-cta:hover { background: #4F46E5; }
.lp-steps-section { padding: 64px 20px; max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; background: #F5F5F7; border-radius: 24px; text-align: center; }
.lp-steps-section h2 { font-size: 26px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 40px; letter-spacing: -0.5px; }
.lp-steps { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 32px; text-align: left; }
@media (max-width: 768px) { .lp-steps { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
.lp-step-num { font-size: 44px; font-weight: 800; color: #EEEFFD; letter-spacing: -2px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
.lp-step h3 { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 8px; }
.lp-step p { font-size: 13px; color: #6E6E73; line-height: 1.6; }
.lp-features { padding: 64px 20px; max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; }
.lp-features h2 { font-size: 26px; font-weight: 700; text-align: center; margin-bottom: 36px; letter-spacing: -0.5px; }
.lp-feature-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); gap: 20px; }
@media (max-width: 600px) { .lp-feature-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
.lp-feature-card { background: #fff; border: 0.5px solid #E5E5E7; border-radius: 14px; padding: 24px; }
.lp-feature-icon { font-size: 24px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
.lp-feature-card h3 { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 8px; }
.lp-feature-card p { font-size: 13px; color: #6E6E73; line-height: 1.6; }
.lp-cta-section { text-align: center; padding: 64px 20px 80px; }
.lp-cta-section h2 { font-size: 24px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 8px; }
.lp-cta-section p { font-size: 14px; color: #6E6E73; margin-bottom: 24px; }
.lp-body { font-size: 14px; color: #3D3D3F; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 14px; }
.lp-detail { max-width: 680px; margin: 64px auto; padding: 0 20px; }
.lp-detail h2 { font-size: 22px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 16px; }
.lp-inline-link { color: #6366F1; text-decoration: none; }
.lp-inline-link:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
</style>
